description: As she ties up her skates for the seemingly millionth time, the U.S. ice dancer Madison Hubbell pictures her routine. A voice in her head reminds her she could make a mistake — then the announcers call her name.
title: Before the Ice Dance, Madison Hubbell Imagines Winning (and Falling)
title_page: Before the Ice Dance, Madison Hubbell Imagines Winning (and Falling) - Video - NYTimes.com
text: Imagine that you’re an Olympic athlete about to compete. How do you calm your nerves? In this series, we take you inside the minds of current and former Olympians as they visualize their dream performance.
